</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-NUGGETS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VAN EXEL, NUGGETS BEAT LAKERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ Sometime this summer, a wrecking ball will knock
McNichols Sports Arena into the pro basketball graveyard, and the
Los Angeles Lakers can only hope any record of Monday night's game
is buried in the rubble.
</P>
<P>
   They didn't just lose, they lost the second straight in a
three-day set. And they didn't just lose to anyone, they lost to
the lowly Denver Nuggets. Worse, the final blows were dealt by the
one Nugget the Lakers least wanted to wreck their road trip.
</P>
<P>
   You remember Nick Van Exel?
</P>
<P>
   The exiled former Lakers guard scored seven of the Nuggets' 13
points in overtime to lead his new team to an astounding 117-113
upset of the team that gave up on him.
</P>
<P>
   Not that Van Exel would gloat or anything, but ...
</P>
<P>
   ``It's great, it's great,'' Van Exel said, then quipped, ``Best
win I've had since I've been in Denver.''
</P>
<P>
   The Nuggets' second win in 10 games came at the expense of a
Lakers team already reeling from a loss 24 hours earlier in
Seattle. And with a flight back to the Pacific Northwest to play in
Vancouver, B.C. tonight, the possibility of an 0-3 road trip _ and
a 6-6 record _ looms like, well, a wrecking ball over the Lakers.
</P>
<P>
   ``Desperation?'' Eddie Jones said, repeating a reporter's
question. ``That's a great word to use. I think a better word is,
we need a win.''
</P>
<P>
   Never mind the math; he's right.
</P>
<P>
   Somehow, despite 26 points and a near triple-double from Kobe
Bryant, 28 points from Shaquille O'Neal, 17 from Jones and a
season-high 24 from Elden Campbell off the bench, the Lakers
coughed up their most embarrassing loss of the season.
</P>
<P>
   ``We lost,'' Bryant said, ``to a team we should have beat by
20.''
</P>
<P>
   They had them by 12, anyway, early in the fourth quarter. But
then Chauncey Billups found a home behind the arc and started
carpet-bombing. Billups hit a trio of 3-point shots and scored 15
points in the fourth, his last 3-pointer concluding a 20-9 run that
gave Denver a 104-103 lead with 54 seconds remaining in regulation.
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal had a chance to regain the Lakers' lead, but he hit only
one of two free throws to tie the game, then fouled out and sent
Antonio McDyess to the line. McDyess missed both free throws and
Campbell got the rebound, only to have it stolen by ... Van Exel.
</P>
<P>
   It hadn't been the best night for Van Exel in regulation _ he
dished out 12 assists, but hit 1 of 12 shots and it appeared his
former team would beat him a second time in 12 days. But he opened
overtime with a 3-pointer and fed Raef LaFrentz on a slam dunk as
the Nuggets pulled ahead.
</P>
<P>
   Without O'Neal, the Lakers tried to win on Campbell's low-post
game, but he went 1 for 4 and had a pair swatted away by McDyess
before fouling out with a 113-106 deficit.
</P>
<P>
   ``Have to give Nick Van Exel a lot of credit,'' coach Del Harris
said of his old nemesis. ``His assisting was spectacular.''
</P>
<P>
   Van Exel was not so charitable. And it was hard to blame him.
Losses like this were once pinned on him.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every time I watch them, I see the same thing, a lack of
intensity.... Same thing we were going through last year. Guys
really aren't having fun out there,'' he said. ``It's beautiful for
me, because I think a lot of people in management and Del thought I
was that problem. And no, I'm not that problem. They know their
problem. They've gotta address that problem.''
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Shaquille O'Neal literally asked to be fined Sunday in
Seattle, and by the time he arrived in Denver on Monday, his wish
had been granted. The NBA fined O'Neal $10,000 for his postgame
rant against officials after the Lakers' 92-89 loss to the Sonics.
Of the fine, O'Neal said, ``Whoop-de-(bleeping)-do. And they can
take 10 (thousand) more, too.... It's just like a tax.... If David
Stern wants to be FICA, he can be FICA.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
