<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Congressional Republicans are reworking
themselves from the impeachment party to the tax cutting party, but
although tax cutting is a cozy comfort zone for Republican
politicians, it is not clear that tax cuts play much better with
the public than impeachment did. (Tom Teepen is national
correspondent for Cox Newspapers.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ An article about bacteria in chicken led to a
conversation with old friends about how we were served chicken when
we were kids. Chicken bacteria wasn't a problem for me. Each Friday
night, I would eat at Grandma's house, she an old-country woman
who, after koshering it in a bath of rock salt, cooked her chicken
so long that no bacteria could hope to survive. (Howard Kleinberg
is a columnist for Cox News Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ Diplomacy is the cruelest art, judging by
Madeleine Albright's ultimatum to the ethnic Albanians _ agree to
the peace agreement or we won't bomb the Serbs. (Rosenfeld, Cox
News Service) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ ANGELINA COUNTY, Texas _ Stopping by the post
office the other morning, I ran into a couple of fellows I've known
since school days. They were excited because their gold shipment
had arrived. It's a Y2K thing _ I wouldn't understand. (Murray, Cox
News Service) MOVED MONDAY.
