   SOCIAL-SECURITY (Washington) _ As Congress prepares to tackle
the ambitious overhaul of Social Security, budget experts tell
congressional committees that President Clinton's plan falls short
of ensuring that the retirement program will be there for baby
boomers. They say that Clinton's plan does not address the basic
fact that the payroll tax dedicated to the retirement fund will not
generate enough money to pay full benefits in the future. By
BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-2000 (Washington) _ Gov. John Engler of Michigan is one of
the Republicans leading the charge to endorse Texas Gov. George W.
Bush as the party's nominee in the 2000 presidential race. By GARY
MARTIN.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-BUZZ (Washington) _ Gov. George W. Bush's deliberations on
