<P>
   FEINSTEIN-MEXICO (Washington) _ Sen. Dianne Feinstein, D-Calif.,
charges that the Mexican government isn't doing enough to root out
corruption and money laundering by drug cartels. But President
Clinton is expected to certify to Congress later this month that
the Mexican government is making good faith efforts in the war on
drugs. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
