   JASPER-TRIAL (Jasper, Texas) _ Jurors convict white supremacist
John William King, 24, in the dragging death of a 49-year-old black
man. Prosecutors called King one of three ``riders coming straight
out of hell.'' By PATTY REINERT and Richard STEWART.
</P>
<P>
   JASPER-KING (Jasper, Texas) _ Did John William King convict
himself with his own words? Before prosecutors received prison
notes King wrote a fellow defendant in which he virtually admitted
to murder, all they had was a drop of blood on his sandal, his
cigarette lighter and DNA on a cigarette at the crime scene.
Defense attorneys raised the premise that both fell out of Berry's
truck and didn't necessarily place King at the scene. By RICHARD
STEWART.
</P>
