governors agreed Tuesday to a plan to urge Congress to rewrite the
Endangered Species Act, a law they say places an unfair burden on
states in the West. Davant
</P>
<P>
   CONNECTICUT -- FUND. Democrats, including Rep. James H. Maloney,
D-Danbury, introduce open-space conservation bill. Maggi
</P>
<P>
   -- COUNSEL. A push has begun in the Senate not to renew a law
that creates independent counsels like Ken Starr. Sen. Christopher
J. Dodd announced today he will not vote to reauthorize the law,
which expires this summer. The Senate Government Affairs Committee,
along with leading Democrat Sen. Joseph I. Lieberman, will be
looking into the law with a series of hearings, starting tomorrow.
Maggi
</P>
