off guard with a question about federal funding of special
education in a meeting at the White House on Monday. Davant
</P>
<P>
   NEVADA -- NUKE. Nevada gained more time Wednesday in its fight
to keep high-level nuclear waste from entering its borders, after a
House committee decided to delay action on legislation that would
force the state to become the nation's steward of spent nuclear
waste. Preston
</P>
<P>
   -- NELLIS. The House Subcommittee on Military Readiness will
conduct a field hearing at Nellis Air Force Base Friday to discuss
budgetary shortfalls at the U.S. military's major combat training
centers. Purvis
</P>
<P>
   PENNSYLVANIA -- INVEST. Project for Philly. More than half of
American families invest in the stock market, making middle-class
investors an increasingly influential group in politics. Fine
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS -- GARZA. Commissioner Garza on his short meeting with
Energy Secretary Bill Richardson. Brown
</P>
<P>
   -- GRANTS. The North American Development Bank awarded grants to
the cities of Alton and Donna for environmental infrastructure
projects. Brown
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN -- MCDONALD-DRUGS. Madison resident Dr. Lynn McDonald
was nominated by Senate Minority Leader Tom Daschle to the newly
created Parents Advisory Council on Youth Drug Abuse. McDonald,
founder of the Families and Schools Together (FAST) program in
Madison, will work with 15 other parents to make recommendations to
the president on drug prevention, education and treatment. Hurt
</P>
<P>
   -- THOMPSON-AMTRAK. As chairman of the Amtrak Reform Board,
Wisconsin Gov. Tommy Thompson has less than a year to prove that
the ailing national passenger railroad can wean itself from
government subsidies by 2002. While his fellow board members praise
the governor's leadership skills, critics claim he has little
chance of succeeding. (Working.) Hurt
</P>
<P>
   WYOMING -- GOVS. Wyoming Gov. Jim Geringer and other western
governors agreed Tuesday to a plan to urge Congress to rewrite the
Endangered Species Act, a law they say places an unfair burden on
states in the West. Davant
</P>
