<P>
   COXNET-WHEELS 0219 -- North American buyers may not immediately
think of Audi when station wagons are mentioned, but the European
manufacturer actually has commonality with those vehicles
traditionally regarded as family haulers _ primarily, change. Like
the new-for-'99 A6 Avant, both Audi and station wagons in general
are putting the past far behind them. (DeVault, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   AT A GLANCE -- Facts about the A6 Avant. (DeVault, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SHARP DRIVING -- The most common perception of the term platform
is it means the vehicles share the same floor plan or metal
stamping that constitutes the ``floor'' of the car. That may be the
case on a shared-platform vehicle, but not necessarily. (Sharp,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
