   STATE LEGISLATIVE NEWS
</P>
<P>
   TEX-LEGIS-CHILDINSURANCE _ AUSTIN _ How poor is not poor enough?
That's the question Gov. George W. Bush and lawmakers are grappling
with as they decide how to structure a government program that
would pay for health insurance for kids whose families are too
wealthy to qualify for Medicaid but too poor to buy private
insurance. At stake is insurance for thousands of Texas families
(of four) who make as much as $33,000 a year. (Greenberger, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   TEX-LEGIS-AUTOINSURANCE _ AUSTIN _ Two state lawmakers want to
do away with the time-consuming and costly way Texas regulates the
price of auto insurance. Sen. Jeff Wentworth and Rep. Harold Dutton
on Tuesday talk about their plan to deregulate the auto insurance
market. (Elizondo, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-VOTERS _ JERUSALEM _ Elections in other countries prompt
efforts to get out the vote. In Israel, they try to fly it in.
Several thousand Israelis in a series of competing, and
semi-secret, political airlifts are expected to come from America
and Europe to cast their ballots in elections this spring. The
influx is apparently a result of three traits that mark the Israeli
character, a dedication to politics, a penchant for traveling and
living outside their country and, finally, a system that does not
allow voting by absentee ballots. As a result, not only are
individual Israelis headed back, but the country's national
airlines is offering election discounts and, reportedly, several
competing groups are looking to charter flights for voters leaning
their way. ``It will be kind of a race between efforts,'' said
Israeli political analyst Daniel Elazar, of the Jerusalem Center
for Public Affairs. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   TURKEY-OCALAN _ ANKARA, Turkey _ Spot coverage of the hearing
for Kurdish rebel leader Abdullah ``Apo'' Ocalan _ a week after the
alleged terrorist and icon to Kurdish separatists was captured in
Nairobi followed by days of bloody protests throughout Europe.
Though things have settled down _ relatively _ here over the last
few days, the closed-door hearing at an island prison brought
expected strong reaction from Kurds. Developing. (Holmes, Cox News
Service).
</P>
