u d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-NY-CHILI-RECIPE-NYT &LR;      02-23 0278
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NY-CHILI-RECIPE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A RECIPE FROM `CHILI NATION': TEXAS BOWL OF RED 
</HEADLINE>
  (With NY-CHILI) 
(nk) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEXAS BOWL OF RED
</P>
<P>
   Adapted from ``Chili Nation'' (Broadway Books, 1998), by Jane
and Michael Stern
</P>
<P>
   Time: 1{ hours
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chopped onions
</P>
<P>
   2 garlic cloves, peeled and minced
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   2 pounds beef round, cut into {-inch cubes
</P>
<P>
   1{ teaspoons salt
</P>
<P>
   1{ teaspoons freshly ground black pepper
</P>
<P>
   1{ teaspoons ground dried Mexican oregano
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon ground cumin
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sugar
</P>
<P>
   5 tablespoons chili powder
</P>
<P>
   1 15-ounce can tomato sauce
</P>
<P>
   Approximately 1\ teaspoons red jalapeno powder (see note) or 1{
teaspoons cayenne pepper
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon masa harina dissolved in { cup water
</P>
<P>
   Sour cream, for garnish
</P>
<P>
   1. In a large skillet or Dutch oven over medium heat, saute
onions and garlic in oil until soft. Add beef, and saute until
browned.
</P>
<P>
   2. Add salt, black pepper, oregano, cumin, sugar and chili
powder; stir well. Stir in the tomato sauce and 1{ cups of water.
Add jalapeno powder or cayenne, beginning with about 1 teaspoon and
gradually adding more to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat
to medium-low. Simmer, partly covered, until beef is tender, about
1 hour and 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   3. Remove pan from heat, and add masa harina mixture. Return to
low heat, and cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Serve
garnished with a tablespoon of sour cream and, if desired, with
beans, rice or bread.
</P>
<P>
   Yield: 4 servings.
</P>
<P>
   Note: Red jalapeno powder may be ordered from Adriana's Caravan
at (800) 316-0820 or (718) 436-8565.
</P>
</TEXT>
