   CANCER-DRUG (Bethesda, Md.) -- The most closely-watched
experimental cancer drug in decades, endostatin, is being made in
large quantities, appears to have no toxic effects in monkeys, and
should enter its first human tests later this year. By Richard
Saltus. 900 words.
</P>
