<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Wednesday, Feb. 24 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-MART (Santa Monica, Calif.) _ The year's biggest event for
Tinseltown's major players comes on March 21 when Academy Awards
are presented; for everyone else, it's Thursday. For hundreds of
mid-level producers, the American Film Market is where the rubber
meets the road as 7,000 participants from 71 countries, including
China for the first time, descend on Santa Monica for nine days. By
Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   LAX-HOMES (Los Angeles) _ There is nothing fancy about the way
real estate analyst Craig M. Silvers predicts housing prices. He
uses a big crystal ball visible from the San Diego Freeway: Los
Angeles International Airport. Silvers measures the change in
passenger traffic through LAX, crunches some numbers and comes up
with an estimate on which direction housing prices will move. By
Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
