<P>
   BODY-PARTS (Ventura, Calif.) _ A mother of five shot her husband
to death, dismembered the body and set the limbs and head on fire
alongside a river, police said Tuesday. Gladis Barreras Soto, 37,
was arrested on suspicion of murder at the home she shared with her
husband and children ages 6 to 11. By Cecilia Chan and Don Holland.
(Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DOG-ATTACKS (Los Angeles) _ Victims were recovering Tuesday
after being attacked by two pit bulls in a Los Angeles
neighborhood. Animal control officers seized one of the dogs
Tuesday after a worker at Robert Frost Elementary School managed to
trap a loose canine in a fenced area and alerted authorities. The
other dog was still on the loose. By Yvette Cabrera. (Will move in
the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   SWEET-CRIME (Los Angeles) _ Never has crime been so sweet.
Burglars broke into The Candy Factory in North Hollywood, bypassing
the computers and other expensive items in favor of $500 in
chocolate. Word has it the cops are looking for kids with sticky
fingers and squeaky voices. By Phil Davis. (Will move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
