official place of residence, mostly in search of better jobs.
Legions of young Chinese are moving one step up the job chain _
those from tiny villages move to small cities to find work, and
those from small provincial cities move to large cities. But rural
migrants remain perpetual outsiders in China's cities, with little
hope of securing the coveted urban residence permits that would
allow them to build an entirely legal life here. By Elisabeth
Rosenthal. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.) With map and
photos. 1,700 words.
