<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GRAMMYS-MULLINS24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On the eve of the biggest night of his career, Atlanta's Shawn
Mullins mulls newfound fame, marriage and the road that got him
there
 &HT;    By Steve Dollar
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Chart busting has its price. Just ask Shawn Mullins
and he'll scribble down the answer. The 30-year-old Atlanta
resident became one of last year's pop music Cinderella stories
after Atlanta modern-rock station 99X (WNNX-FM) began playing his
song ``Lullaby'' last summer. Columbia Records signed him to a
juicy six-figure contract. His tune went Top 10. MTV made him a
familiar face.
</P>
<P>
   But Mullins has been performing so much _ and doing so many
interviews _ that he's put his voice at risk.
</P>
<P>
   The Grammy-nominated Mullins, contending for best male pop vocal
performance for ``Lullaby,'' was trying to keep his pipes in shape
for tonight's big event _ and his seemingly nightly schedule of
gigs. So rather than chat on the phone, we conducted this Q-and-A
session by e-mail and fax while Mullins was on the road in St.
Louis.
</P>
<P>
   By the way, he's not scheduled to sing at the live ceremony in
Los Angeles _ but he may have to make an acceptance speech.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How bizarre does it feel to be going up against fellow
nominees Eric Clapton and Sting?
</P>
<P>
   A: It's pretty crazy _ those two cats I grew up listening to. I
feel totally honored.
</P>
<P>
   Q: If you win, who will you thank first: God, your girlfriend,
Mom and Dad, 99X program director Leslie Fram or Roadie, your dog?
</P>
<P>
   A: My fiancee, Kelly _ probably _ but I don't expect to win.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Are you going to wear the traditional tuxedo or go more the
Pete Buck route? He wore his pajamas when R.E.M. won big a few
years ago.
</P>
<P>
   A: I have no clue what I'm wearing. Probably not a tux and
probably not pajamas (punctuates with a drawing of a smiley face).
</P>
<P>
   Q: Any plans to stop by Ghengis Cohen (the peculiar Chinese
restaurant/deli/coffeehouse where Mullins was inspired to write
``Lullaby'') for a good luck cocktail before the show?
</P>
<P>
   A: I don't think I have time, but if I stop by, I'll have to
grab some Chinese food to go.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I heard that you recently proposed marriage to your
girlfriend and business partner Kelly Hobbs while on a five-day
trip to Paris. You're a romantic son-of-a-gun. How did it feel and
what were your favorite spots?
</P>
<P>
   A: Yea, it was really sweet, quality time with Kel in Paris. I
gave her the ring at the top of the Eiffel Tower. I loved the
cemeteries and museums.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Have you gotten tired of make-up artists fussing with you
yet?
</P>
<P>
   A: Not really, they're all really funny people. They keep the
makeover crap pretty managable. I don't really wear a lot of
make-up so it usually doesn't take much time.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Any good anecdotes about the absurdity of sudden celebrity?
You know, that strange experience of having utter strangers stop
you on the street, famous people call you at home, and seeing your
face on TV screens. After 10 years playing places like Eddie's
Attic, that's got to be a trip.
</P>
<P>
   A: Yea, it is a trip _ it's cool, though. I feel a lot of
support from fans. But, yes, it's strange to be kind of shuffled
into this bizarre power dynamic we call fame.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How bad off is your voice right now and how do you care for
it?
</P>
<P>
   A: It's really not that bad right now _ I've just been singing
and talking a lot. I try not to eat dairy and I don't speak a lot
when I don't have to.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Your thoughts on playing the sold-out Roxy in Atlanta in a
few weeks?
</P>
<P>
   A: Never woulda thunk it. I love the Roxy. I haven't played
there since 1990 with Amy Ray and Kristen Hall and a few others.
I'm totally psyched to be back again.
</P>
<P>
   Steve Dollar writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
