<P>
   RUSSIA-AID (Seattle) _ Northwest exporters have won their first
contracts under an $885 million U.S.-Russia food aid deal,
providing 850 metric tons of dried peas and lentils to help
alleviate anticipated shortages this year in the cash-strapped
nation. Although relatively small, officials says they hope
contracts awarded this week will be the first of several that will
benefit Northwest farmers, exporters and ports that have pioneered
links with the Russian Far East and beyond.
</P>
<P>
   By Ron Redmond. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-MEETS (Seattle) _ Walt Disney Co.'s Michael Eisner treats
shareholders to previews of new animation features and Internet
service at annual shareholders meeting in Seattle. Shareholders
vote down dissident proposals on sweatshop labor, Y2K and poison
pill.
</P>
<P>
   By Bruce Ramsey. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   STARBUCKS-MEETS (Seattle) _ With maps looking like a Pentagon
situation room flashed on a huge screen behind him, Starbucks chief
Howard Schultz stands before a happy house of shareholders in
Seattle and touts the progress in bringing the company's brand of
coffeehouse culture to the rest of the planet.
</P>
<P>
   By Paul Shukovsky. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS (Houston) _ Seattle SuperSonics travel to Houston.
</P>
<P>
   By Ronald Tillery. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBO-VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Baseball's umpires are out of
control.
</P>
<P>
   By Laura Vecsey. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
