<HEADER>
A6561 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LADN-SPORTS-BUDGET- &LR;      02-23 0247
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-SPORTS-BUDGET- </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Feb. 24 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Joe Jares at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
BKC-BARON (Los Angeles) _ Feature/takeout story on Baron Davis, who
might be entering his final regular-season games as a UCLA Bruin.
Davis is showing that he's heeled from knee surgery and that his
game is ready for the NBA. Scouts say he could be a top 15 pick in
the draft this summer if he elects to leave school early. 
By Jon Wilner. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BKC-SCHOOP (Los Angeles) _ USC basketball notebook. 
