<SLUG> BC-GLF-WMATCH-NOTES24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    No sure bets on first day
 &HT;    By Glenn Sheeley
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   CARLSBAD, Calif. _ Tiger Woods vs. Nick Faldo is the most
intriguing match of the Andersen Consulting Match Play's first
round, but probably won't evolve as the most exciting. If logic
prevails, No. 1 Woods should win easily today against the No. 64
player in the field.
</P>
<P>
   Then again, logic and match play are not always companions.
Woods will assume nothing against the three-time Masters champion.
</P>
<P>
   ``He still is dangerous, no matter what,'' Woods said Tuesday.
``Even if he's not up to his usual form, he's still a dangerous
opponent.''
</P>
<P>
   Victimized by Faldo when he collapsed in the 1996 Masters, Greg
Norman said, ``Knowing Nick's mentality and how strong his head is,
he has found ways to win golf tournaments. I wouldn't be at all
surprised if he can find a way to win this ... I wouldn't say
categorically that Tiger is a shoe-in winner.''
</P>
<P>
   Whatever happens, said Nick Price, the gantlet of seven rounds
in five days to make the final will be a challenge: ``Anyone who
wins this week is going to have five great scalps on his belt ...
It's going to be hard to pick up your clubs and play the next week
after this.''
</P>
<P>
   Among the other featured first-round matches:
</P>
<P>
   _ No. 7 Ernie Els vs. No. 58 Paul Azinger: Els has three World
Match Play titles in England and is coming off a win at Los Angeles
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   _ No. 6 Colin Montgomerie vs. No. 59 Craig Stadler: Could be an
upset special.
</P>
<P>
   _ No. 17 Payne Stewart vs. No. 48 Stewart Cink: If Cink wins, he
could face Woods in the third round.
</P>
<P>
   NO DORAL FOR DUVAL
</P>
<P>
   David Duval has withdrawn from next week's Doral-Ryder Open,
needing down time from being on the road since Jan. 4. Woods also
is skipping the Doral.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
