<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Food and lodging for Mr. and Mrs. Aaron
 &HT;    By Maria Saporta
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Henry and Billye Aaron will be guests of President and
Mrs. Clinton at a state dinner tonight for Ghanaian President Jerry
Rawlings. Afterward, they'll spend the night in the White House.
</P>
<P>
   They attended state dinners with former presidents Gerald Ford
and Jimmy Carter, but this is the first time they will have spent
the night in the White House. ``That's why I'm so excited,'' Billye
said. ``I will savor every moment of it.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
