<SLUG> BC-BKC-SCHOOP-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HELP STILL WANTED AT POINT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ With a break in the schedule, USC coach Henry
Bibby spent the weekend in Louisiana, watching high school point
guard Derrick Zimmerman as the Trojans continue their search for a
quality point guard.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-2 Zimmerman, who plays for Monroe Wossman High, is
also being recruited by Mississippi State, Clemson, Alabama and
Tulane.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a rather hot commodity right now,'' recruiting analyst
Bob Gibbons said. ``He's the type of kid that has played better
this season than last summer. He's a academic qualifier and can
really shoot the ball.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every school wanting a point guard is looking at him. He's one
of the top ones still available.''
</P>
<P>
   USC has one scholarship left and would like to sign a point
guard. It continues to be interested in Compton College's James
Jones, who is also being recruited by Washington State and Oregon
State. USC is officially being considered by Long Beach City
College guard Schea Cotton, although Cotton has spurned the Trojans
twice before.
</P>
<P>
   __ Granville questionable: Point guard Brandon Granville
(bruised back) missed practice Monday, although he is expected to
play against Washington on Thursday. Bibby said Granville is
questionable for the game. The freshman injured his back after he
fell hard to the floor while driving to the basket against UCLA.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not sure if he's going to play on Thursday,'' Bibby
said. ``If we had any games (last weekend), he wouldn't have
played.''
</P>
<P>
   __ No arena pitch yet: Although USC's board of trustees and
president Steven Sample have officially agreed to support the
construction of an on-campus arena, Bibby said it is too early to
use the proposed building as a recruiting incentive.
</P>
<P>
   ``We haven't used that,'' Bibby said. ``I think in another year
you're able to use that. That's a starting point for everything and
this is a big plus for the university.''
</P>
<P>
   Now that the arena project has some support from the
administration, the biggest obstacle will be obtaining financing.
USC is hoping to sell the naming rights to the arena, meaning it
will eventually have a company's name for its title a la the
Staples Center.
</P>
<P>
   __ Winning season?: USC (12-11, 4-10) needs to sweep its home
games against the Washington schools to ensure a winning record,
but Bibby said the Trojans' record doesn't necessarily reflect what
he already considers a successful season.
</P>
<P>
   ``Who's to say we've had a winning season?'' Bibby said. ``I say
we've had a winning season. The kids have not quit. I'm pleased.
Success is not always wins and losses. The guys have done a good
job.''
</P>
</TEXT>
