   OBIT-COHEN (New York) _ Bessie Cohen, who as a 19-year-old
seamstress escaped the deadly Triangle Shirtwaist fire in which 146
of her co-workers perished in 1911, died on Sunday in Los Angeles.
She was 107 and was the last survivor of the Manhattan fire,
according to the Union of Needletrades, Industrial and Textile
Employees. By Michael T. Kaufman.
