brand of moderate congressional Republican he represents _ that
small faction that suddenly loomed large when it changed the shape
of this month's impeachment vote _ sometimes seems an endangered
species, teetering on the edge of what some have called dodo-like
extinction as the party has become more conservative across the
country. Across the country, that is, except in New England. By
