</P>
<P>
   GRAMMY-GREENE (New York) _ A profile of Michael Greene, often
embattled head of the Grammies. By Neil Strauss.
</P>
<P>
   SCULPTURE-RETURN (New York) _ More than 15 years ago the Asia
Society learned that its collection contained a 1,000-year-old
Indian relief sculpture that had been stolen from a provincial
museum in Dhubela, in central India. Last week, after many
intermittent discussions, the society worked out the details of its
return with Indian officials and joined the small but growing
number of museums that are voluntarily surrendering items of
cultural heritage, sending them back to their countries of origin.
By Judith H. Dobrzynski.
</P>
